column5: looks like the stator in my 92 rude 150 went, need one before the weekend anyone have any leads
Sandy Cove marine in Barrie used to stockpile tons of old outboard parts.  Dont know if they still do since reopening after bankruptcy.  Might be worth a try.

Try Dave Sullivan @ City Marine (Etobicoke) 416 207 0344. He's usually got used parts kicking around (I know he's got my used/good stator from my Merc 115 kicking around). Tell him Simon referred you. And if you don't mind, ask him if my boat's gonna be ready this weekend
thanks guys went with the only person that could get it thursday for me and called me back had to get a new unit 440 bones
